{
  "question_id": "611f2ef1-6e5b-43fe-b05c-b02836f54e3b",
  "short_text": "Square Root of a Number",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a number `N` and prints the **Square Root** of `N`.\n\n<MultiLineNote>\n\nTo calculate the **Square Root** of `N`, use the `N` power **0.5** (**N<sup>0.5</sup>**).\n\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be a single line containing a float that is the **Square Root** of `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 4`,\n\n- The **Square Root** of `N` is **2.0** (**4<sup>0.5</sup> = 2.0**).\n\nThe output should be **2.0**.\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "fbf53937-10ca-42ef-8622-d28f31fd50d9",
      "code_content": "number = int(input())\n\nresult = number ** 0.5\nprint(result)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
